The '''Taiwan bamboo partridge''' ('''''Bambusicola sonorivox''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Phasianidae]]. It is endemic to [[Taiwan]].  It was formerly considered a subspecies of the [[Chinese bamboo partridge]].<ref>Species delimitation in the Chinese bamboo partridge ''Bambusicola thoracica'' (Phasianidae; Aves). Chih-Ming Hung et al., Zoologica Scripta Vol. 43, Issue 6, p. 562–575, November 2014, {{doi|10.1111/zsc.12071}}</ref>

It has several [[onomatopoeic]] names known among [[Taiwanese indigenous peoples]]: ''tkurih'' ([[Seediq language|Seediq]] and [[Truku language|Truku]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://e-dictionary.ilrdf.org.tw/sdq/terms/211051.htm|title=tkurih|author=原住民族語言研究發展基金會|work=原住民族語言線上詞典|access-date=2023-09-16|language=trv , zh-tw}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://e-dictionary.ilrdf.org.tw/trv/terms/521883.htm|title=tkurih|author=原住民族語言研究發展基金會|work=原住民族語言線上詞典|access-date=2023-09-16|language=trv, zh-tw}}</ref> ''tikulhat'' ([[Thao language|Thao]]), ''tikulas'' ([[Bunun language|Bunun]]), ''tjikulai'' ([[Paiwan language|Paiwan]]),<ref>{{cite book|author=周明傑|chapter=力與美的交織－五個部落的排灣族勇士舞研究|editor=行政院原住民族委員會|year=2007|title=2007全國原住民族研究論文集|publisher=行政院原住民族委員會|pages=(1-8-)1-(1-8-)27|url=http://www.tipp.org.tw/research_article.asp?F_ID=61771&FT_No=8|language=zh-tw}}</ref> and ''tikolac'' ([[Amis language|Amis]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://acd.clld.org/cognatesets/30013#5/15.974/122.648|title=*tikuRas: a bird, the Formosan bamboo partridge|last1=Blust|first1=Robert|author-link=Robert Blust|last2=Trussel|first2=Stephen|website=Austronesian Comparative Dictionary|date=2010|publisher=Max Planck Institute for Evolutionary Anthropology|access-date=8 November 2022}}</ref>

